      "message": "a flag argument is usually a code smell and makes code much more difficult to maitain: https://martinfowler.com/bliki/FlagArgument.html\n\nI prefer to clean this code a bit, instead `unconditionally` flag pass a function that filters which images to load, then create two functions\n\n```\nlazyLoadImages: function($container) {\n  loadImages( $container, function shouldLoadImage ($placeholder) .... //is around view port);\n```\n\nand\n\n```\nloadAllImages: function( $container ) {\n  loadImages( $container, () \u003d\u003e { return true; } );\n```\n\nAlso, my concern is that from the implementation I assume that this function can be called twice, this is kind\u0027a scary because at the end of this function we listen to scroll, resize, section-toggled events, which shouldn\u0027t happen if we load all images uncoditionally (all images are there, there is no readon to load them).\n\nThose listeners should be registered in `lazyLoadImages()` and not in `loadAllImages()`",
